	"summary": "Security update for slurm_17_11",
	"details": "This update for slurm_17_11 fixes the following issues:\n\n- CVE-2020-27745: Fixed potential buffer overflows from use of unpackmem() (bsc#1178890).\n- CVE-2020-27746: Fixed a potential leak of the magic cookie when sent as an argument to the xauth command (bsc#1178891).\n- Fixed %posttrans macro _res_update to cope with added newline (bsc#1153259).\n- Fixed permissions of slurmdbd.conf (bsc#1155784).",
